author: HYUNG-JIN KIM and JOE McDONALD Associated Press
title: Governments face more pressure to curb virus economic damage
description: South Korea has reported fewer than 10 new coronavirus cases for the first time in two months as U.S. governors ease lockdowns amid pressure worldwide from businesses and the public to limit the pandemic’s economic damage
content:
SEOUL, South Korea -- 
South Korea reported fewer than 10 new coronavirus cases Sunday for the first time in two months as U.S. governors ease lockdowns amid pressure worldwide from businesses and the public to limit the pandemic's economic damage.
